# Build State

Tracks the status and history of each target across builds. State is scoped per output directory and persisted under `.intentc/state/{output-dir}/`.

## TargetStatus

Enum of possible states for a target:
- `pending` ‚Äî never built
- `built` ‚Äî successfully built
- `failed` ‚Äî last build failed
- `outdated` ‚Äî built, but a dependency has changed since

## BuildStep

A single phase within a build. Captures what happened and how long it took.

- `Phase` (string) ‚Äî name of the phase (e.g. "resolve_deps", "build", "validate")
- `Status` (string) ‚Äî "success" or "failure"
- `Duration` (duration) ‚Äî wall-clock time
- `Summary` (string) ‚Äî human-readable description of what happened

## BuildResult

The outcome of building a single target.

- `Target` (string) ‚Äî feature path
- `GenerationID` (string) ‚Äî unique identifier for this build run
- `Status` (TargetStatus) ‚Äî resulting status
- `Steps` (list of BuildStep) ‚Äî ordered phases
- `CommitID` (string) ‚Äî checkpoint ID from the VCS capturing all changes (new files, modifications, deletions) produced by this build
- `TotalDuration` (duration) ‚Äî sum of step durations
- `Timestamp` (datetime) ‚Äî when the build completed

## StateManager

Manages per-target state for a given output directory. Depends on a `VersionControl` instance for checkpointing changes.

- `GetStatus(target) -> TargetStatus` ‚Äî returns current status; `pending` if unknown
- `GetBuildResult(target) -> BuildResult or null` ‚Äî last build result, null if never built
- `SaveBuildResult(target, result)` ‚Äî persist result, update status
- `SetStatus(target, status)` ‚Äî override status (e.g. mark outdated)
- `MarkDependentsOutdated(target, project)` ‚Äî walk the DAG and set all descendants to `outdated`
- `Reset(target)` ‚Äî clear all state for a target
- `ResetAll()` ‚Äî clear all state for the output directory
- `ListTargets() -> list of (target, status)` ‚Äî all tracked targets

## VersionControl

An abstract interface for checkpointing file changes. Implementations produce a unique ID (SHA, UUID, etc.) for each checkpoint that can be used to inspect or restore changes.

- `Checkpoint(message) -> string` ‚Äî snapshot current changes, return a unique commit/checkpoint ID
- `Diff(fromID, toID) -> string` ‚Äî return the diff between two checkpoints
- `Restore(commitID)` ‚Äî restore the output directory to the state at a given checkpoint
- `Log(target?) -> list of commitIDs` ‚Äî list checkpoints, optionally filtered by target

### GitVersionControl

Concrete implementation backed by git. Uses commits on a build-managed branch. The checkpoint ID is the git SHA.

## Persistence

State is stored as a single JSON file per output directory at `.intentc/state/{output-dir}/state.json`. The schema is versioned. Unknown fields are tolerated on read. Missing files return empty/default state ‚Äî never errors.

## Build Log

An append-only log at `.intentc/state/{output-dir}/build-log.jsonl`. Each line is a JSON object representing a completed BuildResult. This provides full audit history independent of the mutable state file.
